{
  "texts": [
    "Both models were quantized to 4-bit precision using NF4 format and equipped with LoRA adapters.",
    "DRaFT-Q operated on top of this baseline setup by dynamically adjusting adapter ranks and applying token-level reward weighting during training.To test DRaFT-Q's generalizability and scalability, we extended it to LLaMA-2-7B and LLaMA-2-13B.",
    "The 7B models were trained on the same T4 setup with reduced steps, while the 13B experiments were conducted on a 40GB-class NVIDIA L40 GPU.",
    "These larger-scale runs were used for timeline tracing and behavior analysis, particularly to observe rank reallocation patterns, loss stabilization, and adaptation convergence under tighter schedules.",
    "The experiments confirmed that DRaFT-Q can scale to significantly larger models without requiring architectural modifications or fine-tuning restarts."
  ]
}